  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( \\dfrac{x^2 - 9}{x + 3} = x^2 - 3 \\) by cancelling the \\( x \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> You may only cancel FACTORS, not terms. A weak answer cancels the \\( x \\)'s; a strong answer factorises \\( (x+3)(x-3) \\) and cancels the bracket to get \\( x - 3 \\).</p>",
