  "reading": "<p><strong>0 marks:</strong> \\( 0.696 \\) as the answer to \\( \\frac{2}{5-\\sqrt{2}} + \\frac{1}{5+\\sqrt{2}} \\) — a decimal on an \"exact\" question.</p><p><strong>Full marks:</strong> \\( \\frac{15+\\sqrt{2}}{23} \\), the surd form. If unsure, write the exact form <em>and</em> the decimal — the exact form earns the marks and the decimal never loses them.</p>",
