  "readingTitle": "explain — The 'exact' command word",
  "reading": "<p><strong>0 marks:</strong> \\( x = 1.47,\\ -7.47 \\) on an \"exact\" question — decimals only.</p><p><strong>Full marks:</strong> \\( x = -3 \\pm 2\\sqrt{5} \\). If unsure, write the exact form <em>and</em> the decimal — the exact form earns the marks and the decimal never loses them.</p>",
