  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "explain — 'Hence' means reuse part (a)",
  "reading": "<p>If part (b) says \"<em>Hence</em> solve \\( \\text{f}(x) = 0 \\)\", start from your completed-square form \\( (x+3)^2 - 20 = 0 \\) — do <strong>not</strong> reach for the quadratic formula. The 2024 examiners noted candidates who restarted (or converted back to the original) wasted time and risked errors.</p>",
  "question": "Part (b) says 'Hence solve'. You should:",
