  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Doing the long division correctly but writing no 'Quotient =' or 'Remainder =' answer</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> The final mark is for IDENTIFYING both results. A weak answer stops after the working; a strong answer states the quotient AND the remainder explicitly, filling in both answer lines.</p>",
