  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Dividing \\( 2x^3 - 5x + 1 \\) by \\( x - 1 \\) without a place for the missing \\( x^2 \\) term</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Insert a \\( 0x^2 \\) placeholder. A weak answer mis-aligns the columns and makes subtraction slips; a strong answer writes \\( 2x^3 + 0x^2 - 5x + 1 \\) so every power lines up.</p>",
