  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( x^2 + x^3 = x^5 \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> These are unlike terms and cannot be combined; the answer is just \\( x^3 + x^2 \\). A weak answer adds the indices; a strong answer only adds indices when MULTIPLYING, e.g. \\( x^2 \\times x^3 = x^5 \\).</p>",
