  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> On a 'detailed reasoning' question, quoting the three factors straight from a calculator.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> DR needs the method seen: show \\( \\text{f}(a)=0 \\) and obtain the quadratic factor. A weak answer gives factors only (0 marks); a strong answer shows every step.</p>",
  "question": "A DR factor-theorem answer with no working scores:",
