  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "tip — Turn a percentage into a multiplier",
  "reading": "<p>For modelling questions, convert the rate to a multiplier: a rise of \\( r\\% \\) gives \\( \\left(1 + \\frac{r}{100}\\right) \\); a fall of \\( r\\% \\) gives \\( \\left(1 - \\frac{r}{100}\\right) \\). So \\( 3\\% \\) growth is \\( 1.03 \\) and \\( 15\\% \\) depreciation is \\( 0.85 \\). Then the model is simply \\( x_{n+1} = (\\text{multiplier})\\,x_n \\).</p>",
