  "pageName": "9.2 Definite Integrals and Areas",
  "source": "mcq",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "question": "\\( \\int_{-2}^{2}(x^2 - 4)\\,dx = -\\tfrac{32}{3} \\). The physical area between the curve and the \\( x \\)-axis is:",
